Taphura sauliensis
Boulard 1971 : 688
(type material in MNHN).

subSubSection.paragraph: Remarks. The claspers are bifurcated at their terminus and bent towards the midline. The basal pygofer lobes are rounded finger-like extensions.

Distribution. The species is currently known from
French Guiana
, Colombia , and Peru (Duffels & van der Laan 1985 ; Sanborn 2013 ). The distribution of the species is expanded here to included Ecuador and
Trinidad & Tobago
.
